# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Reference issuer / status service — the interim FIDUCIARY + revocation authority.
# This service holds the PRIVATE signing key: the whole revocation authority.
#
# HOW TO USE
#  • Local run:  works with NO env (generates an ephemeral key + listId per process).
#                Copy to `.env` (gitignored) only if you want durable local custody.
#  • Railway:    paste the real values into the issuer service's Variables.
#
# SECRETS: never put the real ISSUER_SIGNING_KEY / FIDUCIARY_TOKEN in THIS file —
# it is committed. Real, pre-generated values live in the gitignored deploy secrets
# file (bridle/scratchpad/path-a-secrets.txt).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Durable signing key (REQUIRED for a hosted deploy) ───────────────────────
# EC P-256 PKCS8 PEM — the revocation authority. Without it the service generates
# a new key per restart, changing the trust anchor Bridle pinned at boot and 404ing
# every prior status.uri. Accepts a real-newline OR \n-escaped PEM.
# COLLECT: pre-generated → copy ISSUER_SIGNING_KEY from path-a-secrets.txt.
# ISSUER_SIGNING_KEY="-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\n...\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----\n"

# ── Stable status-list id (REQUIRED for a hosted deploy) ─────────────────────
# Any UUID. Keeps published status.uri paths stable across restarts.
# COLLECT: pre-generated → copy ISSUER_LIST_ID from path-a-secrets.txt.
# ISSUER_LIST_ID=

# ── Issuer namespace ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The `iss` stamped into signed lists + grant issuance signatures.
# ISSUER_ISS=https://interim-fiduciary.kilbowieconsulting.com/h2a/issuer

# ── Fiduciary token (REQUIRED) ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# Gates POST /revoke AND POST /sign-grant. MUST match the console's FIDUCIARY_TOKEN.
# COLLECT: pre-generated → copy FIDUCIARY_TOKEN from path-a-secrets.txt.
# FIDUCIARY_TOKEN=

# ── Durable revoked set (OPTIONAL) ───────────────────────────────────────────
# JSON file on a PERSISTENT VOLUME so live revokes survive a restart (else the
# revoked set is in-memory). On Railway, attach a volume and point this at it.
# ISSUER_REVOKED_PATH=/data/revoked.json

# ── Port (managed by the platform) ───────────────────────────────────────────
# Default 8790; Railway injects its own PORT and the service honours it.
# PORT=8790
